@RTK.md

## FlexNetOS runtime ownership

`/home/flexnetos/.nix-profile` is the sole installed binary, configuration,
state, cache, runtime, launcher, and compatibility frontdoor for Claude,
Codex, and Yazelix. The profile-owned Claude frontdoor generates reviewed
configuration into `/run/user/1001/yazelix/profile-runtime/claude`. Never
create or use a parallel home-owned agent directory, raw store payload, or
generated source tree as an active owner.

## Persistent memory (ICM) — mandatory

Recall before work:

```nu
icm recall "query"
icm recall "query" -t "topic-name"
icm recall-context "query" --limit 5
```

Store immediately when an error is resolved, an architecture decision is made,
an owner preference is discovered, a significant task completes, or a long
session needs a progress checkpoint:

```nu
icm store -t errors-resolved -c "description" -i high -k "keyword1,keyword2"
icm store -t decisions-project -c "description" -i high
icm store -t preferences -c "description" -i critical
icm store -t context-project -c "summary" -i high
```

Use `icm health`, `icm topics`, and topic-filtered recall to preserve topic
hygiene. Do not store secrets, transient build logs, or routine status output.
